      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Test this Triple for equality with another Object.

        If the Object to be tested is not a Triple, then this method returns false.

        Two Triples are considered equal if and only if both the names and first values are equal.

        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
